title: Excitation functions for 7Be, 22,24Na production in Mg and Al by deuteron irradiations up to 50 MeV

x4freetext: Excitation functions for 7Be, 22,24Na production in
Mg and Al by deuteron irradiations up to 50 MeV

x4codes.hlp: Institute for Nuclear Research (ATOMKI), Debrecen, Hungary

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.70, p.2763 (2012)

x4codes.hlp: Catholic Univ. of Louvain, Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium

x4freetext: Magnesium foils (Goodfellow, purity 99.8%, nominal
thickness  275 um) and aluminum foils (Goodfellow,
purity 99.8%, nominal  thickness 49.06 um).
Two stacks
containing magnesium foils (Goodfellow, purity 99.8%,
nominal thickness 275 microns)
and aluminum foils (Goodfellow, purity
99.8%, nominal thickness 49.06 microns) were
irradiated at the external beam line of the CGR960
cyclotron in Louvain la Neuve (LLN, Belgium)
with deuterons of 50 MeV incident energy.
energy. The beam was monitored by Ti (10.9 microns)
The stacks contained also Ni and C foils. The
activity was measured without chemical separation by
high resolution gamma-ray spectroscopy. The effective
energy for each foil was determined using the
energy-range formula and tables of Andersen and
Ziegler, and corrected by comparing the
simultaneously re-measured cross sections of the
monitor reactions to the latest recommended values.
The activities were determined from the photo-peak
areas, taking into account corrections for decay
during irradiation, waiting and measuring time. Decay
data and Q-values of the reactions were taken from
NUDAT and from Q-value calculator of NNDC. Ni and Ti
foils were used also as catcher foils for the recoiled
reaction products. Corrections was made for the
recoil effect.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.174, p.235 (2001)

x4freetext: The uncertainty on the median energy in the
foils is increasing along the stack and includes the
cumulative effects of the uncertainty of incident
beam energy (+-0.2 MeV), uncertainty on stopping in
each foil due to thickness (5%) and straggling
effects. The overall estimation is an uncertainty of
+-0.2 MeV for the first foils increasing to +-2.5 MeV
in the last foil in which still significant
cross-section values could be calculated.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The uncertainty of the cross-sections were
estimated taking the independent relative
errors of the linearly contributing components,
number of the bombarding particles, number of the
target nuclei, decay data, detector efficiency and
peak area were summed quadratically, and the square
root of the sum was taken. The uncertainties of the
cross-sections were estimated to be 10-13%.
The experimental data were compared to the
results of the theoretical model codes TALYS, EPIRE-D
and ALICE-D.
The measured experimental data were compared
to those found in the literature.
Fitted excitation functions were used for
determination of integral physical yields. Depth
distribution of the produced 22Na was calculated at
11.2MeV bombarding deuteron energy for TLA studies.
